parameters:
\n<Rui>The forest...? Could it be that we've made it
outside?
\n<Tuberose>Yes. Thank you for the perfect score reaction.
\n<Tuberose>Mufufu, it's a prank! A huge success!

\n<Tuberose>After crossing over to this world, I've been
looking into various subcultures, and I've always
wanted to try this once.

\n<Tuberose>This is a part of the world you saved. Does that
make sense to you?

\n<Rui>...Another world!? Are you really saying this is
Roots?

\n<Tuberose>Not at all. The Eternal Dream Training Hell Game
is a power beyond even my control. It's
immeasurable.

\n<Rui>...Isn't it a hassle to say that long name every
time you explain it?
\n<Tuberose>Cool things come with their appropriate costs!

\n<Rui>I see... So what do I need to do here to be
considered cleared?

\n<Tuberose>I have summoned a boss deep in the forest.
Defeating that boss means you clear it.
\n<Rui>I get it. Just need to knock them down.

\n<Tuberose>However, this is a game. To ensure the game is
fair, your powers should be limited to some
extent.

\n<Rui>...Indeed. I can use my powers, but it feels like
when I first became Sol.

\n<Rui>Still, everything seems to be at my
disadvantage... What kind of game makes you go
through such roundabout measures?

\n<Rui>If you think this kind of thing is fun, you're
going to lose friends, you know.

\n<Tuberose>...Did you just naturally say those words just
now?

\n<Rui>...Well, it seems I don't have a choice, so I'll
play along.

\n<Rui>Just remember, if you die when I clear this, it's
not my fault.

\n<Tuberose>As expected of Rui-san! Even if you get thoroughly
ravished by monsters, I'll still take you as my
bride!

\n<Tuberose>Then I shall await you in the infernal dungeon.
Please rampage to your heart's content.
\n<Rui>Hmph, I'll clear this quickly and be back.
